title._content: Arnott's Biscuits' Albion van, Sydney, ca. 1935-1940 / photographer Milton Kent

description._content: Known for their beautiful fire engine red livery and the colours of the rosella, an Arnott's van is a fond memory of many Australians. The iconic brand was bought out in 1997 by Campbells. William Arnott, the founder of Arnott's, had tried his luck on the goldfields in 1851 and failed, only to become rich with his bakery. Come to the Library and see other miners trying their luck in our free exhibition of the UNESCO-listed Holtermann photographic collection, or view it online at : www.sl.nsw.gov.au/events/exhibitions/2013/holtermann/inde... Format: Photograph Find more detailed information about this photographic collection: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/item/itemDetailPaged.aspx?itemID=421397 From the collection of the State Library of New South Wales www.sl.nsw.gov.au
